#Approach:

Largest Subarray with Sum 0 – Prefix Sum + HashMap Approach

Is problem me hum prefix sum use karte hain.
Hum running sum calculate karte hain aur HashMap me store karte hain
ki kaunsa prefix sum kis index par pehli baar aaya tha.

Agar running sum kabhi 0 ho jaye, iska matlab starting se current index tak ka subarray sum 0 hai.

Agar koi prefix sum dobara mil jaye,
to iska matlab beech ka subarray ka sum 0 hoga.
Isliye current index - previous index se subarray ki length nikalte hain
aur max length update karte hain.

Important:
HashMap me prefix sum ka sirf first occurrence store karna hai,
kyunki hume longest subarray chahiye.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int maxLen(int[] arr) {
        // Your code goes here
        HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        int maxLen = 0;
        int sum = 0;

        for(int i=0; i<arr.length; i++){
            sum += arr[i];
            if(sum == 0){
                maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, i+1);
            }

            if(map.containsKey(sum)){
                int len = i - map.get(sum);
                maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, len);
            }else{
                map.put(sum, i);
            }
        }
        return maxLen;
    }
}
